item.title: Nike Air Max Woven Boot
item.dc:creator: chedemo
item.content:encoded:
By and large, Nikes Air Max offerings lean toward sporty, technical styles, but the brands NikeLab imprint just dropped a versatile Air Max sneaker that looks just as good with trousers as it does with sweatpants.
The NikeLab Air Max Woven Boot combines an all-over woven upper with full-length Max Air cushioning. While this sort of hybrid style isnt uncharted territory for the brand, its rarely executed as seamlessly as this look.

item.dc:creator: chedemo
item.content:encoded:
Here's everything you need to know for the NikeLAB Air Max 1 Pinnacle Sail. All available retailers will also be updated via this page. Keep it here for all the latest updates as well as exclusive stockist info.
NikeLAB continues their Pinnacle legacy by releasing yet another series of exclusive and luxurious designs. While you can opt for for colourful styles, this full monochromatic theme is expected to be hugely popular.
At first glance, this looks to be an off-white colourway, but Sail is actually a slightly darker shade. This extends onto the complimentary midsole underfoot which also features a tonal shade across the Air Unit.
Elsewhere and everything remains true to the Air Max 1. It features that same iconic overlapping construct of leather as well as the swoosh across the sidewall and embossed branding at the rear. A leather logo tab on the tongue also distinguishes this as an exclusive.

item.content:encoded: The shoe would be making its long-awaited debut almost a year to the day since the Swoosh first unveiled it at its Innovation Summit last year (you can see the reveal video below.) Since then, weve also had confirmation that COMME des GARONS has been working with NikeLab on its own version of the shoe.The heavily-cushioned silhouette takes Nikes Air Max technology to the next level by replacing the usual foam outsole with one made entirely from air bubble cushioning. item.title: Nike Air Max Jewell
item.dc:creator: chedemo
item.content:encoded:
The Nike Air Max Jewell is one of Nikes newest womens models. Although it recently made its debut, Nike already had big plans for the silhouette starting off with this Nike Air Max Jewell Tortoise Shell Pack.
Unlike the first couple of colorways that have dropped, this pair ditches the mesh construction in favor of something with a little more luxe appeal to them. The new look of the shoe has them dressed in tonal one-piece leather uppers. Accentuating the premium look of the shoe are features such as the embroidered Nike Swoosh branding and the faux tortoise shell shank support that extends all the way up to the heel region.What does remain the same is the Air Max cushioning on the heel region of the sole.

item.title: Converse
item.dc:creator: chedemo
item.content:encoded:
Iconic Profile, Built to Skate The Converse CONS One Star Pro Suede Backed Canvas delivers the durability and impact protection needed for any style of skateboarding with suede-backed canvas construction and plush Nike Lunarlon cushioning. The low profile offers total flexibility, while the rubber sole enhances boardfeel and grip. Benefits
  • Gusseted tongue for comfort and a snug fit
  • Nike Lunarlon foam for cushioning
  • CONS traction rubber for powerful grip
  • Canvas sits on top of durable suede
One Star Origin In 1974, Converse launched a low-cut suede version of the Chuck Taylor All Star with a simple but impactful style change: a solitary star became the statement on the sneaker's lateral side. Reissued in the early '90s, the One Star soon rose to prominence in alternative culture, embraced by self-reliant innovators of street and skate.

  • Nike Lunarlon foam for cushioning
  • CONS traction rubber for powerful grip
